          <msContents>
            <summary>2 brief alchemical works whose titles translate as The book of revelation and illumination and Encoded proof, written by a father for his son. The writer identifies himself only as a student of Jaʻfar al-Ṣādiq. A code is used occasionally in the manuscript, and a key is included (f. 3r).</summary>
            <textLang>Arabic</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Kitāb al-Kashf wa-al-bayān</title>
              <respStmt>
                <resp>former owner</resp>
                <persName>Aga Khan, Sadruddin, Prince, 1933-</persName>
              </respStmt>
            </msItem>
          </msContents>
          <physDesc>
            <objectDesc>
              <supportDesc material="paper">
                <support>
                  <p>paper</p>
                </support>
                <extent>9 leaves : 152 x 105 mm. bound to 157 x 109 mm</extent>
                <collation>
                  <p>Paper, i (later paper) + 9 + i (later paper); 1⁹; 348-365, pagination in ink, upper outer corners.</p>
                </collation>
              </supportDesc>
              <layoutDesc>
                <layout>Written in 20-27 long lines.</layout>
              </layoutDesc>
            </objectDesc>
            <scriptDesc>
              <scriptNote>Written in cursive script.</scriptNote>
            </scriptDesc>
            <decoDesc>
              <decoNote>Drawing in red and black ink of laboratory equipment, including mortar and pestle, furnace, and glass containers (f. 9v); significant or coded words and phrases and drawing captions in red ink.</decoNote>
              <decoNote n="9v">Drawing, Alchemical equipment, f. 9v</decoNote>
            </decoDesc>
